How to build primesieve (Windows, Linux, Mac OS X)
==================================================

  1. Download and install Qt
    Qt is a C++ cross-platform application and UI framework by nokia
    that is available under the GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE. primesieve
    has been developed with Qt4 and requires Qt 4.4 or above.

    Download and install the latest version of the Qt SDK from:
    http://qt.nokia.com/downloads
    Old versions can be obtained from (once Qt4 is not supported
    anymore):
    ftp://ftp.trolltech.com/qt/source/

  2. Launch the Qt-primesieve.pro file with Qt-Creator (cross-platform
    IDE that is part of the Qt SDK). Have a look at
    Qt-Creator-build-settings.png for the build settings.

Remarks
=======

  1. The compiled primesieve executable depends on the QtGui4 and
    QtCore4 libraries (Windows: .dll, Unix: .lib). You must copy these
    libraries into the executable directory if you want to run it on
    other PCs.

  2. SSE 4.2 POPCNT instruction
    primesieve counts prime numbers slightly faster if it is compiled
    with support for the SSE 4.2 POPCNT (bit population count)
    instruction. For GNU GCC (>= 4.4) use the -mpopcnt option.
